<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="286" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="21.[160,1155,662,757]" box="[160,252,662,688]" pageId="21" pageNumber="286">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,252,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="286">Ecology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[160,1155,662,757]" pageId="21" pageNumber="286">Specimens found mating and laying the egg masses on unidentified species of hydrozoans at night, and inactive at the base of the colonies during the day.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="286" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="21.[160,1155,807,902]" box="[160,300,807,833]" pageId="21" pageNumber="286">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,300,807,833]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="286">Distribution</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[160,1155,807,902]" pageId="21" pageNumber="286">
<collectingCountry box="[160,258,842,867]" name="Morocco" pageId="21" pageNumber="286">Morocco</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Tamsouri N &amp; Carmona L &amp; Moukrim A &amp; Cervera JL" box="[271,501,842,867]" pageId="21" pageNumber="286" pagination="991 - 997" refId="ref22381" refString="Tamsouri N, Carmona L, Moukrim A, Cervera JL. 2014. Description of a new species of Piseinotecus (Gastropoda, Heterobranchia, Piseinotecidae) from the northeastern Atlantic Ocean. Bull Mar Sci. 90: 991 - 997. doi: 10.5343 / bms. 2014.1019." type="journal article" year="2014">Tamsouri et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
); 
<collectingCountry box="[521,568,842,867]" name="Italy" pageId="21" pageNumber="286">Italy</collectingCountry>
(Ballesteros et al. 2012–2021), Catalonia (
<bibRefCitation author="Ballesteros M &amp; Madrenas E &amp; Pontes M" pageId="21" pageNumber="286" pagination="1 - 28" refId="ref18028" refString="Ballesteros M, Madrenas E, Pontes M. 2016. Actualizacion del catalogo de los moluscos opistobranquios (Gastropoda: Heterobranchia) de las costas catalanas. Spira. 6: 1 - 28." type="journal article" year="2016">Ballesteros et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
; this study).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="286" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[160,1155,951,1081]" box="[160,262,951,977]" pageId="21" pageNumber="286">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,262,951,977]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="286">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[160,1155,951,1081]" pageId="21" pageNumber="286">
Originally described from 
<collectingCountry box="[459,560,987,1012]" name="Morocco" pageId="21" pageNumber="286">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, it is quite widespread on the Catalan coast. Differs from similar-looking species, such as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Montagu, 1816)" baseAuthorityName="Montagu" baseAuthorityYear="1816" box="[589,1013,1021,1046]" class="Gastropoda" family="Flabellinidae" genus="Edmundsella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="21" pageNumber="286" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pedata">
<emphasis box="[589,813,1021,1046]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="286">Edmundsella pedata</emphasis>
(Montagu, 1816)
</taxonomicName>
, by the presence of abundant white spots in the cerata, rhinophores and oral tentacles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
